'''Domo arigato''' is a [[Japan|Japanese]] expression that translates to "Thank you." Knowledge of the expression was popularized in the Western world at least in part by the song [[Mr. Roboto]] which features the line "''Domo arigato'', Mr. Roboto."

The line has been used as a pop culture reference a number of times, including in the film 'Austin Powers in Goldmember' and cartoons Futurama and The Simpsons.